## What Was Built

Prevented silent data loss when `BILLAR_DB_PATH` is unset. CLI and MCP now resolve a durable per-user SQLite path by default while preserving explicit override.

### Requirements Delivered (11/11 spec scenarios compliant)

| Requirement | Status |
|-------------|--------|
| Explicit Path Override (`BILLAR_DB_PATH` honored when non-empty) | ✅ |
| Whitespace-only `BILLAR_DB_PATH` treated as unset | ✅ |
| XDG_DATA_HOME default (`$XDG_DATA_HOME/billar/billar.db`) | ✅ |
| UserConfigDir fallback (`os.UserConfigDir()/billar/billar.db`) | ✅ |
| HOME final fallback (`$HOME/.local/share/billar/billar.db`) | ✅ |
| Default directory creation (mode 0700) | ✅ |
| Directory creation failure surfaces actionable error | ✅ |
| No resolvable base → config error with `BILLAR_DB_PATH` hint | ✅ |
| CLI wired to `cfg.DBPath` (no direct env read for DB open) | ✅ |
| MCP wired to `cfg.DBPath` (no direct env read for DB open) | ✅ |
| `sqlite.Open("")` preserved for tests (ephemeral temp DB) | ✅ |
| README + `.env.example` document resolution order and override | ✅ |

